AGI - A choice of freedom. Matteo Salvini defends without hesitation Roberto Vannacci and gives orders to hiss to cease any controversy on the candidacy of the general to Europeans. "If on the left they run, and have the right to do so," Ilaria Salis, "a girl with very heavy accusations in a foreign prison, I do not see why we should not run" Vannacci, "a general who fought with his boys, in Lebanon, in Iraq>", says the Leghist secretary, obliged to respond to his choice after the opposition manifested by some party bigeds, like Giancarlo Giorgetti and Massimiliano, The head of Via Bellerio defends the general also on the phrases on "classes with separate characteristics" for the disabled, who raised a dust and forced some, like the ministra Alessandra Locatelli, to specify that "the League is for inclusion".
&nbsp;
"It seems to me a storm over nothing, on words that have been deliberately misunderstood - says Salvini - In September with the ministers of school and disability we assumed 13 thousand teachers of support. We're working to destroy the architectural barriers. It should be included. If there are very serious disability, the support teacher is not enough. Having special boys in class is an added value." The Secretary of the League confirms that he will not run for Europe. "I do the minister. I take care of the commuters, of the Code of Road, of the Italian houses with the Home Plan. I have 18 hours a day to take care of a ministry that is of all Italians, not right or left. I'll do my campaign, but I didn't feel like running for it," he said.
&nbsp;
"I do not comment on the choices of others, if Giorgia Meloni, Antonio Tajani, Elly Schlein and Carlo Calenda have chosen to apply well," he adds to the next day of the announcement that Meloni will be in the field. "I have the awareness of creating a team with strong candidates - reassuring - made also of people who do not have the League card in their pockets. I think of Vannacci but also of entrepreneurs and professionals who have our idea of Europe which is different than that of the left but also of that of our allies of the center-right". For the rest, in the party, today is the day of the landing in the Chamber of the ddl on the Autonomia, after the free way of the Senate. In Montecitorio there is a show of the Leghista pride, with the Brescian deputy Simona Bordonali who wears a 'green padano' t-shirt with the written 'Il Vento del Nord' and asks that the law also bears the name of Roberto Maroni, besides that of Roberto Calderoli.
<h2> The first output together
Meanwhile, there is wait for Tuesday (30 April) when Salvini will make the first public release with Vannacci on the occasion of the presentation in Rome of his book, 'Controvento'. Qualified sources of Via Bellerio argue that the federal secretariat has left the order not to miss the appointment. The presentations of the book take place in all stages of the election campaign and in several have the opportunity to participate in the territory. The event would be dedicated above all to the Romans, therefore, no 'precept' on the presence. But the Leghista secretary would have been categorical - some sources report - on the attitude expected by his regarding Vannacci's candidacy: not express judgments or criticisms in public, newspapers or TV. As often happens, the line explicit Andrea Crippa.
&nbsp;
"Roberto Vannacci is a candidate of the League for Europeans on June 8-9, although he does not have the party card. But it has very similar ideas to ours and is making a strong contribution turning Italy with the aim of having a Europe different from the current one. The message must be clear: you win all together and you lose all together," says Salvini's deputy. "I'm sure internal polemics don't help the League. We already have against television, almost all newspapers and the maximum systems - adds Crippa - The internal polemics certainly do not help the League to change Europe. But, I repeat, be clear from today: do not pass the message that if we win we are all good and if we lose he lost Salvini. You win or you lose all together." Waiting to see what contribution will give the candidacy of Vannacci to the party (some speak of 1.5%; others even 3%), the lists of the League were closed on weekends, with calls 'last minute' to several women to 'reflect' the female quota previewed by law alternating with that male.
Other names
In the North West, where it is estimated that two/three MEPs will be elected, for example, a 'sacrifice' was asked to the Lombard Councillor Elena Lucchini and to the deputation Bordonali, both candidates. Together with Angelo Ciocca, Silvia Sardone, Isabella Tovaglieri, Gianna Gancia and others. In the North-East district will run the deputy mayor of Treviso Alessandro Manera, the outgoing Venetian Euro MPs - the Veronese Paolo Borchia and the Venetian Rosanna Conte -, the deputy and mayor of Pozzonovo Arianna Lazzarini, the first citizen of Porto Tolle Roberto Pizzoli and Morena Martini, mayor of Rossano veneto; in addition to the Emilia-Romagna But also the mayor of Monfalcone (Gorizia) Anna Maria Cisint, Councillor Fvg Stefano Zannier and the outgoing MEP Elena Lizzi, member of the Committee on Employment and Social Affairs.
&nbsp;
Vannacci will be candidate in all constituencies, but it is not clear who will be the leaders in those in the North. The general - officially communicated the League - will guide the list to the Center, constituency in which should be candidates also Laura Cartaginese, group leader in the Lazio Region, former councilman Davide Bordoni, and the outgoing Euro MP Susanna Ceccardi. In the South is certain the candidacy of Aldo Patriciello, sample of preferences that at the end of 2023 left Forza Italia and joined the League. While, in the Islands, driving the list will be the outgoing congressman Annalisa Tardino, in front of Raffaele Stancanelli, Mimmo Turano, Senator Nino Germanà, Francesca Reitano. At Udc, Ester Bonafede.

