High representatives of countries and international institutions were invited to take part in the summit: present the Emiratina Presidency of Cop 28 and Cop29 of Azerbaijan, Brazil as the G20 Presidency and, as part of the focus on Africa, Mauritania as the Presidency of the African Union, Kenya, Algeria and the African Development Bank. The work will also see the participation of international organizations such as Aiea, Irena, Odi, Conference on Climate Change, Undp, Ocse, Unep and Office of the Secretary General of the United Nations for Climate. Over one hundred and fifty are the information operators accredited to the Media Center di&nbsp;Venaria&nbsp;Reale.

